decks.notes: The main concept of this deck is to control the game by ramping up quickly with Azusa, Lost But Seeking and various land ramp spells to get ahead on mana. The deck aims to overwhelm opponents with powerful spells like Emrakul, the Promised End and Ugin, the Spirit Dragon, while also utilizing control elements like Oblivion Stone and All Is Dust to deal with threats on the board. The inclusion of cards like Crucible of Worlds and Ramunap Excavator allows for recursive land plays, while also being able to tutor up key lands like Dark Depths with cards like Expedition Map. Overall, the deck aims to dominate the game through powerful spells and efficient land ramp.
